'''Sannomiya Jinja''' (三宮神社) is a Shinto shrine located in {{ill|Sannomiya-chō (Kobe City)|de|Sannomiya-chō (Kobe City)|ja|三宮町 (神戸市)|lt=Sannomiya-chō|lt_ja=三宮町|lt_de=Sannomiya-chō|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Sannomiya-chō (Kobe City)|qq=}}, [[:en:Chūō-ku, Kobe|Chuo Ward]], [[:en:Kobe|Kobe]], in [[:en:Hyōgo Prefecture|Hyōgo Prefecture]]. It is the third among the eight shrines collectively known as the {{ill|Ikuta Eight Sub-shrines|de|Ikuta Eight Sub-shrines|ja|生田裔神八社|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Ikuta Eight Sub-shrines|qq=}}, each of which enshrines one of the offspring deities of [[:en:Ikuta Shrine|Ikuta Shrine]]. The chief deity of this shrine is {{ill|Takitsuhime-no-Mikoto|de|Takitsuhime-no-Mikoto|ja|湍津姫命|1=Tagitsuhime|2=ja|3=タギツヒメ|4=zh|5=多岐都比賣命|6=fr|7=Tagitsuhime|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Takitsuhime-no-Mikoto|13=User:Immanuelle/Tagitsuhime|qq=}}.
This shrine also gave its name to the surrounding area known as “Sannomiya.”
